    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1085"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1085">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760h.68/7–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1085<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31">July 31
                            [1945.]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. Department is instructing Embassies Moscow and London to inform <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOffs1">FonOffs</gloss> of our recommendation of appointment of
                    tripartite commission in accordance with <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 392, July 28,<note n="1" xml:id="d1085fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1081">Document No. 1081</ref>.</note> and to solicit
                    indication by <gloss target="#t_FonOffs1">FonOffs</gloss> of agreement of Soviet
                    and British Governments to collaborate in this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
